00:33:19,540 --> 00:33:21,820
Turn over there in 2 Corinthians chapter number four

434
00:33:21,820 --> 00:33:26,400
in verse number 18, Paul shares with us a powerful truth

435
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:30,380
with regard to his life and his own testimony

436
00:33:30,380 --> 00:33:33,980
and really the encouragement to these in Corinth.

437
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:37,220
And what a powerful truth for us to conclude with here

438
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:40,580
this evening, to understand the importance and the purpose

439
00:33:40,580 --> 00:33:42,580
by which God has placed us here.

440
00:33:42,580 --> 00:33:47,580
We find in 2 Corinthians four in verse number 17,

441
00:33:47,580 --> 00:33:49,020
he says, for our light affliction,

442
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,340
which is but for a moment,

443
00:33:50,340 --> 00:33:52,500
worketh for us a far more exceeding

444
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,020
and eternal weight of glory.

445
00:33:54,020 --> 00:33:57,260
See, there's something for us after death.

446
00:33:57,260 --> 00:33:58,080
Amen?

447
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:01,500
Death is simply a doorway to the presence of God

448
00:34:01,500 --> 00:34:03,540
and being with Him for all of eternity.

449
00:34:03,540 --> 00:34:05,100
And we find that, listen,

450
00:34:05,100 --> 00:34:06,740
they sang the song this morning,

451
00:34:06,740 --> 00:34:08,740
little is much when God is in it.

452
00:34:08,740 --> 00:34:10,220
And in that song, it talks about

453
00:34:10,220 --> 00:34:11,980
there's a crown that you can win.

454
00:34:11,980 --> 00:34:14,420
The Bible records for us five crowns

455
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:17,060
that can be obtained by the people of God.

456
00:34:17,060 --> 00:34:19,180
And you read Revelation four,

457
00:34:19,180 --> 00:34:21,020
and you see how that they cast Him

458
00:34:21,020 --> 00:34:22,500
at the feet of the Lord.

459
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:24,500
And what power, listen, the lost man,

460
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:27,180
he's just living for today.

461
00:34:27,180 --> 00:34:29,860
He has nothing that he's looking forward to.

462
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:32,940
He has no hope of eternity.

463
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:35,120
We find here, Paul continues,

464
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:38,540
while we look not at the things which are seen,

465
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:40,420
but at the things which are not seen.

466
00:34:41,820 --> 00:34:44,540
For the things which are seen are temporal.

467
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:48,120
The things which are not seen are eternal.

468
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:51,720
Oh, that God would help us to have an eternal perspective.

469
00:34:51,720 --> 00:34:54,720
That we'd understand as we read Genesis four

470
00:34:54,720 --> 00:34:56,280
and Genesis five,

471
00:34:56,280 --> 00:35:01,000
such a contrast between these two genealogies,

472
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,800
the ungodly line of Cain,

473
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,960
the godly line of Seth.

474
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:08,760
And you notice what God chooses to record

475
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,080
about each of those lines of people

476
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:13,480
and their generations.

477
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:16,940
This evening, oh, that we'd be numbered

478
00:35:16,940 --> 00:35:19,640
with those that would be called the godly.

479
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:22,460
That we would call upon the Lord,

480
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:25,480
trust Him, depend upon Him, worship Him.

481
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,100
That we'd walk with Him.

482
00:35:27,100 --> 00:35:28,620
That we'd please Him.

483
00:35:28,620 --> 00:35:30,620
That it could be said of us

484
00:35:30,620 --> 00:35:34,780
that we found grace in the eyes of the Lord.

485
00:35:34,780 --> 00:35:36,220
We're living in a time today,

486
00:35:37,460 --> 00:35:39,460
we don't need to be tainted by the world

487
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:40,820
as I preached this morning.

488
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:44,820
What we need is to be able to stand

489
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:49,300
and to stand in the power of His might.

490
00:35:49,300 --> 00:35:51,220
And to be able to stand against

491
00:35:51,220 --> 00:35:53,460
the wickedness in high places.

492
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:57,920
Standing in His strength

493
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:00,020
and pleasing Him with our lives.

494
00:36:00,020 --> 00:36:01,980
We see in Genesis four and five,

495
00:36:01,980 --> 00:36:05,000
these two genealogies and what a contrast they are.

496
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:05,840
Let's pray together.

